        "timestamp": "2020-08-24 19:06:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDaniel, Roy, FYI, we have some requirements where we would be a little more strict if something is not configured quite right, or the controller at initialization time fails to come up properly.  This would mean that the JVM will exit for example if a configured controller is not properly set up at boot up.   This in turn will cause k8s to reattempt and so on.",
        "patchset_number": 2
